<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-10T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="984" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d984">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.85/4–1046: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Pawley</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">u.s. urgent</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-10T19:00:00-05:00">April 10, 1946—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>331. Approval has been given by Dept to sale from surplus of following
                            vessels to Peru (your 372 Apr 1<note n="15" xml:id="d984fn15">Not
                                printed.</note>). You may inform Peruvian authorities. Navy Dept has
                            informally discussed matter with Peruvian representatives.</p>
                        <list>
                            <item>6 Submarine chasers (SC)</item>
                            <item>8 Landing Craft, Infantry, (Gunboat) (LCI(G))</item>
                            <item>2 Oilers (AO)</item>
                            <item>2 Rescue Tugs (ATR)</item>
                            <item>10 Landing Vehicles, tracked (LVT)</item>
                            <item>1 Gunboat (PG)</item>
                            <item>3 Landing Craft, tank (LCT)</item>
                        </list>
                        <p>Symbols in parentheses refer to Navy nomenclature for vessels
                            concerned.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>